  "datePublished": "2026-04-27",
  "description": "The school's load-bearing structural claim: late-liberal governance is operationally closed in Niklas Luhmann's specific sense. No coherent subject-position produces an outside, because every 'outside' is itself a genre running on the same affective infrastructure. The closure is descriptive sociology, historically specific to platformal-energetic conditions, not totalizing of all human life.",
  "name": "The Operational Closure of Late-Liberal Governance",
